<paragraph blockId="12.[136,1451,266,365]" pageId="12" pageNumber="139">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,241,266,292]" pageId="12" pageNumber="139">Uredinia</emphasis>
hypophyllous, scattered, individual or grouped, circular, subepidermal, erumpent, brown. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1270,1451,266,292]" pageId="12" pageNumber="139">Urediniospores</emphasis>
ovoid, ellipsoidal to broadly ellipsoidal, or reniform, (18–)22–26(–27) × (15–)16–18(–20) µm (n = 30), pale yellow, wall 1–2 µm thick, echinulate, with 4–5 inconspicuous, more or less equatorial germ pores. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1166,1224,338,364]" pageId="12" pageNumber="139">Telia</emphasis>
not observed.
</paragraph>
